5\u20131828) |trans-title=History of modern Hellenism, Volume VII: The Great Greek Revolution (1821\u20131829) - The African simoom, or Ibrahim's raid in Greece (1825\u20131828) | location = Thessaloniki | year = 1986 | ref=harv|language=el}}\n* {{cite book | last=Vakalopoulos | first=Apostolos E. | script-title=el:\u0399\u03c3\u03c4\u03bf\u03c1\u03af\u03b1 \u03c4\u03bf\u03c5 \u03bd\u03ad\u03bf\u03c5 \u03b5\u03bb\u03bb\u03b7\u03bd\u03b9\u03c3\u03bc\u03bf\u03cd, \u03a4\u03cc\u03bc\u03bf\u03c2 \u0397\u2032: \u0397 \u039c\u03b5\u03b3\u03ac\u03bb\u03b7 \u0395\u03bb\u03bb\u03b7\u03bd\u03b9\u03ba\u03ae \u0395\u03c0\u03b1\u03bd\u03ac\u03c3\u03c4\u03b1\u03c3\u03b7 (1821\u20131829) - \u0399\u03c9\u03ac\u03bd\u03bd\u03b7\u03c2 \u039a\u03b1\u03c0\u03bf\u03b4\u03af\u03c3\u03c4\u03c1\u03b9\u03b1\u03c2, \u03ae \u03b7 \u03b5\u03c0\u03ce\u03b4\u03c5\u03bd\u03b7 \u03b3\u03ad\u03bd\u03b5\u03c3\u03b7 \u03c4\u03bf\u03c5 \u03bd\u03b5\u03bf\u03b5\u03bb\u03bb\u03b7\u03bd\u03b9\u03ba\u03bf\u03cd \u03ba\u03c1\u03ac\u03c4\u03bf\u03c5\u03c2 (1828\u201327 \u03a3\u03b5\u03c0\u03c4. 1831) |trans-title=History of modern Hellenism, Volume VIII: The Great Greek Revolution (1821\u20131829) - Ioannis Kapodistrias, or the painful birth of the modern Greek state (1828\u201327 Sept. 1831) | location = Thessaloniki | year = 1988 | publisher = Emm. Sfakianakis & Sons | ref=harv|language=el}}\n* {{cite book|first=Apostolos E.|last=Vacalopoulos|year=1975|title=The Greek Nation, 1453\u20131669: the Cultural and Economic Background of Modern Greek Society|publisher=Rutgers University Press|isbn=0-8135-0810-X}}\n* {{cite book|first=Jan Hendrik Willem|last=Verzijl|year=1968|title=International Law in Historical Perspective|volume=VI|publisher=[[Martinus Nijhoff Publishers]]|isbn=90-286-0223-2}}\n{{Refend}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Wikisource|Greek Declaration of Independence}}\n{{Commons category}}\n* [http://www.ahistoryofgreece.com/revolution.htm Greek War of Independence]\n* [https://www.questia.com/PM.qst?a=o&d=4911867 The Question of Greek Independence: A Study of British Policy in the Near East, 1821\u20131833]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20150402112930/http://300spartanwarriors.com/articlesandreviews/greekindependence.html The relevance of the 300 Spartans to the Greek War of Independence]\n* {{Cite EB1911|wstitle=Greek Independence, War of|last=Phillips |first=Walter Alison |authorlink=Walter Alison Phillips |short=x}}\n* [http://imslp.org/wiki/Oh!_Mount_Thy_Bright_and_Gallant_Steed_(Hewitt,_John_Hill) Oh! Mount Thy Bright and Gallant Steed]\n\n{{Greek War of Independence|state=collapsed}}\n{{Greece topics}}\n{{Symbols of Greece}}\n{{Rebellions in the Ottoman Empire}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Greek War Of Independence}}\n[[Category:Greek War of Independence| ]]\n[[Category:1820s conflicts]]\n[[Category:1820s in Greece]]\n[[Category:1820s in the Ottoman Empire]]\n[[Category:19th-century rebellions]]\n[[Category:March observances]]\n[[Category:Greek culture]]\n[[Category:Greek society]]\n[[Category:Wars involving Greece]]\n[[Category:Wars involving the Ottoman Empire]]\n[[Category:Wars involving France]]\n[[Category:Wars involving Russia]]\n[[Category:Wars involving the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:History of Ayval\u0131k]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|War of independence waged by Greek revolutionaries}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2012}}\n{{Infobox military conflict\n| conflict          = Greek War of Independence\n| image             = File:Greek_revolution_collage.jpg\n| image_size        = 300px\n| caption           = '''Clockwise:''' The camp of [[Georgios Karaiskakis]] at [[Phalerum|Phaliro]], the burning of an Ottoman frigate by a Greek [[fire ship]], the [[Battle of Navarino]] and [[Ibrahim Pasha of Egypt]] at the [[Third Siege of Missolonghi]]\n| date              = 21 February 1821 \u2013 12 September 1829{{Greece Old Style dating}}<br />({{Age in years, months, weeks and days|month1=02|day1=22|year1=1821|month2=09|day2=12|year2=