ekadventurelo0000howa|url-access=registration|publisher=Atheneum|isbn=0-689-10653-X}}\n* {{cite book|last=Jelavich|first=Barbara|title=History of the Balkans, 18th and 19th centuries|publisher=Cambridge University Press|location=New York|year=1983|isbn=0-521-27458-3|url-access=registration|url=https://archive.org/details/historyofbalkans0000jela}}\n* {{cite book|first=Kyriakos|last=Kassis|year=1979|title=Mani's History|location=Athens|publisher=Presoft}}\n* {{cite book|first=John S.|last=Koliopoulos|year=1987|title=Brigands with a Cause: Brigandage and Irredentism in Modern Greece, 1821\u20131912|publisher=Clarendon|isbn=0-19-888653-5}}\n* {{cite book |title=Greece: the Modern Sequel |last=Koliopoulos |first=John S. |author2=Veremis, Thanos M. |year=2004 |publisher=C. Hurst & Co. Publishers |isbn=1-85065-463-8|chapter=A Regime to Suit the Nation}}\n* {{cite journal |last1=Krimbas |first1=Costas B. |year=2005 |title=Greek Auditors in the Courses of Jean Lamarck |journal=The Historical Review |volume=2 |pages=153\u2013159 |url=http://www.historicalreview.org/index.php/historicalReview/article/view/187/83 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110723063050/http://www.historicalreview.org/index.php/historicalReview/article/view/187/83 |archivedate=23 July 2011 |df=dmy-all }}\n* {{cite book|first=Mark|last=Mazower|year=2004|title=Salonica, City of Ghosts: Christians, Muslims and Jews, 1430\u20131950|location=London|publisher=HarperCollins|isbn=0-00-712023-0}}\n* {{cite book|first=Andrew James|last=McGregor|year=2006|title=A Military History of Modern Egypt|publisher=Greenwood Publishing Group|isbn=0-275-98601-2|chapter=Egypt in the Greek Revolution|url=https://archive.org/details/militaryhistoryo00andr}}\n* {{cite book|first=William|last=Miller|year=1966|title=The Ottoman Empire and Its Successors|publisher=Routledge|chapter=The War of Greek Independence|isbn=0-7146-1974-4}}\n* Miller, Marion S. \"A 'Liberal International'? Perspectives on Comparative Approaches to the Revolutions in Spain, Italy, and Greece in the 1820s.\" ''Mediterranean Studies'' 2 (1990): 61\u201367. [https://www.jstor.org/stable/41163980 online]\n* {{cite book |last= Milton |first=John |author2=Diekhoff, John Siemon |title=Milton on himself|publisher=Cohen & West |year=1965 |page=267 |oclc=359509 }}\n* {{cite book |editor1-first=Vassilis |editor1-last=Panagiotopoulos |title=History of Modern Hellenism |volume=III |year=2003 |publisher=Ellinika Grammata |location=Athens |language=Greek |isbn=960-406-540-8}}\n:* Papageorgiou, Stephanos P. \"The First Year of Freedom\". pp. 53\u201372.\n:* Theodoridis, Georgios K. \"A Modern State\". pp. 125\u2013142.\n:* Tzakis, Dionysis \"The Military Events (1822\u20131824)\". pp. 73\u2013102.\n* {{cite book|first1=Constantine|last1=Paparrigopoulos|author1-link=Constantine Paparrigopoulos|last2=Karolidis|first2=Pavlos|author2-link=Pavlos Karolidis|year=1925|location=Athens|title=History of the Hellenic Nation|publisher=Eleftheroudakis}}\n* {{cite book|first1=Petros|last1=Pizanias|title=The Greek revolution of 1821 : a European event|isbn=9754284253|year=2011}}\n* {{cite book|first=Brancha|last=Rivlin|year=1988|title=The Holocaust in Greece|url=http://www.zchor.org/greece/jewry.htm|publisher=Keterpress Enterprises Jerusalem}}\n* {{cite book|first=Christian|last=Roy|title=Traditional Festivals|url=https://archive.org/details/traditionalfesti0000royc|url-access=registration|publisher=ABC-CLIO|year=2005|isbn=1-57607-089-1|chapter=Annunciation}}\n* {{cite book|first=William|last=St. Clair | author-link=William St Clair | url=http://www.openbookpublishers.com/reader/3 | title=That Greece Might Still Be Free \u2013 The Philhellenes in the War of Independence|doi=10.11647/OBP.0001|edition=2nd Edition 2009|publisher=Open Book Publishers|year=2008 |isbn=9781906924003 }}\n* {{cite book|first=L.S.|last=Stavrianos|year=2000|title=The Balkans since 1453|publisher=C. Hurst & Co. Publishers|isbn=1-85065-551-0|chapter=Age o